English: I believe I have reached my limits...
Spanish: Creo que de aquí no paso...
PortugueseBr: Creio que este é meu limite.

Japanese: ひと休みさせてもらおう…。
English: I need to get some rest...
French: Il faut que je me repose...

English: I'm going to lay low for a while.
German: Ich leg mich eine Weile hin...

English: Any reason you are not attacking...?
Spanish: ¿Me dirás por qué ya no atacas?
Arabic: هل من سبب لامتناعك عن الهجوم؟

English: Are you devising a plan then?

Don't just stand there!
Let us fight!
French:
Reste pas là comme ça !
Il faut combattre !
German:
Steh nicht einfach rum!
Lass uns kämpfen!
Russian: Не стой без дела! Пора в бой!
Arabic:
لا تقف هناك فقط!
دعنا نقاتل!

Japanese: ムム…一度そちらへ戻ろう。
English: Very well, I shall join you.
German:
Nun gut, ich werde
an deiner Seite sein.

Japanese: 一旦貴殿に合流しよう。
助かったよ、ありがとう。
貴殿のフォローに救われたよ。
English: I'm glad I've got you with me.
Italian: Sono lieta di averti con me.
German: Ich bin froh, dass du da bist.
Russian: Я рада, что ты со мной.
PortugueseBr: Fico feliz de ter você comigo.

Japanese: 少し待っていてくれたまえ！

English:
I've just had a flash
of inspiration.
French:
Je viens d'avoir
un éclair de génie.
Italian:
Ho appena avuto un barlume
di ispirazione.
SimplifiedChinese: 我突然想到一个好点子！
Arabic:
لقد خطر لي وميض
من الإلهام.

Japanese: しばらくここは任せたよ！
English: I'll leave things to you for a while.
French: Je te laisse gérer un peu.
Italian:
Lascio tutto in mano a te,
per un po'.
German:
Ich überlasse die Dinge
hier für eine Weile dir.
Russian: Пока оставлю тут все на тебя.
Polish:
Na jakiś czas tutejsze
sprawy zostawiam tobie.
PortugueseBr: Deixo as coisas por sua conta.

Japanese: 待たせた分、活躍しよう！
English: Let's make up for lost time!
German: Holen wir die verlorene Zeit auf!
TraditionalChinese: 久等了，換我來大顯身手！
SimplifiedChinese: 让你久等啦，我会好好表现！

Japanese: ちょっとしたサプライズさ！
